@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam boxPadding 8
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderThickness 2
skinparam noteBorderColor #888888
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFDD
skinparam ParticipantBorderThickness 1.5
skinparam ArrowColor #444444
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam SequenceMessageAlignment left

title RIMA PoC - Table of Contents (ToC) Flow\nTask 579 / June 2026

actor "User" as user #LightBlue
participant "MapComponent\ntemplate" as mapTpl #E8F5E9
participant "TocComponent" as tocComp #F3E5F5
participant "arcgis-layer-list\n[Web Component]" as layerList #FFEBEE
participant "MapViewService\n[Signal]" as viewSvc #E8F5E9
participant "ArcGIS MapView" as mapView #FFEBEE
participant "ArcGIS Layer" as layer #FFEBEE

== Component Initialisation ==

mapTpl -> tocComp : Angular renders <rima-toc>\nin MapComponent template
activate tocComp

note over tocComp
  TocComponent constructor:
  - injects MapViewService
  - resolves viewChild('layerList')
    -> reference to <arcgis-layer-list> element
  - registers Angular effect() watching
    viewService.mapView() signal
end note

tocComp -> layerList : Template renders:\n<arcgis-layer-list\n  #layerList\n  show-heading\n  show-filter\n  selection-mode="single"\n  visibility-appearance="checkbox"\n  (arcgisTriggerAction)="onTriggerAction($event)"\n>
activate layerList

note over layerList
  At this point the layer list is empty.
  It requires a MapView reference before
  it can display any layers.
end note

== Reactive Binding (triggered by MapView registration) ==

viewSvc -> viewSvc : writableMapView.set(view)\n[signal emits from MapComponent.initMap()]

note over tocComp
  Angular effect() fires because
  viewService.mapView() signal changed.
  Runs inside untracked() to prevent
  re-triggering on layerList changes.
end note

tocComp -> layerList : layerList.view = mapView
tocComp -> layerList : layerList.listItemCreatedFunction =\n  onListItemCreated callback

layerList -> mapView : reads map.layers collection
layerList -> layerList : builds list items from\nmap layer hierarchy\n(GroupLayer -> nested items,\n FeatureLayer/WMTSLayer -> leaf items)

== List Item Creation (per layer) ==

group For each layer in the map
  layerList -> tocComp : listItemCreatedFunction({ item })
  activate tocComp

  alt item.layer.type === 'feature' OR 'wmts'
    tocComp -> layerList : item.actionsSections = [\n  [{ title:'Zoom to',\n     icon:'zoom-to-object',\n     id:'zoom-to-layer',\n     type:'button' }]\n]
    note right of layerList
      Adds a "Zoom to" action button
      to the layer's context menu.
      Only FeatureLayer and WMTSLayer
      entries receive this action.
    end note
  else other layer types (GroupLayer, etc.)
    tocComp -> layerList : no action added
  end

  deactivate tocComp
end group

note over layerList
  Layer list is now fully populated.
  User sees:
  - Hierarchical layer tree (GroupLayers as folders)
  - Checkboxes to toggle layer visibility
  - Filter/search input
  - "Zoom to" buttons on feature/WMTS layers
end note

== User Interaction: Toggle Visibility ==

user -> layerList : clicks checkbox on a layer
layerList -> mapView : layer.visible = true/false
note over mapView : ArcGIS SDK immediately\nshows/hides the layer on the map

== User Interaction: Zoom to Layer ==

user -> layerList : clicks "Zoom to" action button
layerList -> tocComp : (arcgisTriggerAction) event\n{ action: { id:'zoom-to-layer' },\n  item: { layer } }
activate tocComp

tocComp -> tocComp : onTriggerAction(event)\ncheck: action.id === 'zoom-to-layer'
tocComp -> viewSvc : read mapView() signal
viewSvc --> tocComp : MapView reference

tocComp -> layer : [ASYNC] layer.load()
activate layer
note right of layer
  Ensures layer metadata
  (including fullExtent)
  is fully loaded from server.
end note
layer --> tocComp : layer loaded
deactivate layer

alt layer.fullExtent exists
  tocComp -> mapView : [ASYNC] view.goTo(layer.fullExtent)
else layer.type === 'wmts' (fallback)
  tocComp -> mapView : [ASYNC] view.goTo(\n  layer.activeLayer.fullExtent)
else no extent available
  tocComp -> tocComp : no navigation (silent)
end

deactivate tocComp

note over user
  Map animates to the selected
  layer's spatial extent.
end note

@enduml
